      <aside class="row article-comments" style="overflow: hidden;">
    <div class="row">
            <h2 class="comment-section-head hidden-xs">Comments (22)</h2>
                                                <div class="col-sm-12 forum-comment">
    <div class="row">
        <a href="https://forums.appleinsider.com/profile/hmlongco"><img loading="lazy" class="user-avatar" src="https://vanillicon.com/v2/d50883f6407a2841713e2dc47bc283a9.svg" alt="Forum User hmlongco" style="display: inline-block;">
        <h2 style="display: inline-block;">hmlongco</a></h2>
        <span>said about <time datetime="2020-08-06T13:11:32+00:00">1 year ago</time></span>
        <p><p>Custom silicon for AI and ML, image processing, video decoding and encoding.... THAT is what is going to differentiate Apple's notebooks and desktops in the years to come.<br><br>I watched a video not too long ago where someone was doing 4K video editing, color grading, and rendering in real-time... on an iPad Pro. And for the most part the silly thing wasn't even breathing hard.<br><br>That's on an A12z that's about two-generations behind in process and performance, and on a device where it's throttled due to battery-life constraints and thermal&nbsp;management. But also where the capability is made possible by doing much of the work in custom silicon.<br><br>I really can't wait to see what comes out of this...</p>
</p>
    </div>
    <hr>
</div>
                                                                <div class="col-sm-12 forum-comment">
    <div class="row">
        <a href="https://forums.appleinsider.com/profile/SpamSandwich"><img loading="lazy" class="user-avatar" src="https://vanillicon.com/v2/43acbb6b6fa048d1a00725d3b61eae9f.svg" alt="Forum User SpamSandwich" style="display: inline-block;">
        <h2 style="display: inline-block;">SpamSandwich</a></h2>
        <span>said about <time datetime="2020-08-06T15:18:31+00:00">1 year ago</time></span>
        <p><blockquote class="Quote">
  <div class="QuoteAuthor"><a href="https://forums.appleinsider.com/profile/217746/hmlongco" rel="nofollow ugc">hmlongco</a> said:</div>
  <div class="QuoteText">Custom silicon for AI and ML, image processing, video decoding and encoding.... THAT is what is going to differentiate Apple's notebooks and desktops in the years to come.<br><br>I watched a video not too long ago where someone was doing 4K video editing, color grading, and rendering in real-time... on an iPad Pro. And for the most part the silly thing wasn't even breathing hard.<br><br>That's on an A12z that's about two-generations behind in process and performance, and on a device where it's throttled due to battery-life constraints and thermal&nbsp;management. But also where the capability is made possible by doing much of the work in custom silicon.<br><br>I really can't wait to see what comes out of this...</div>
<p>
In a mere ten more years it&rsquo;ll be shocking how much computing power will be on-device and available to consumers.</p></blockquote>
</p>
    </div>
