        <span>said about <time datetime="2020-08-06T15:48:23+00:00">1 year ago</time></span>
        <p><p>This article is so important to understanding Apple.&nbsp; There is so much packed into a few brief paragraphs.<br><br>We hear people complain/predict that Apple doesn't "get" AI and can't succeed because:<br>1. No one wants to work at Apple before they are handcuffed by privacy concerns.<br>2. Siri sucks and it's never get better because no one cares.<br>3. Apple won't be able to compete with Google because of Apple's limited notions about where/how to process the information.<br><br>Here's a world-class talent who chose to leave Google to head up these activities at Apple and he (with apparent sincerity) believes that this is all nonsense and (apparently) is getting stuff done at Apple to address deficiencies he's identifying.<br><br>So next time someone here pulls up some example from 3 years ago about why Apple is going to fail and AI, my reaction is going to be "is that before or after this dude took over" and "is that dude still working at Apple."&nbsp; Color me optimistic.</p>
</p>
